DataElement.preferredName: Biological Entity Part Quantity Range ISO21090.URG.INT.POS.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: An integer falling within minimum and maximum bounds that specifies how many parts that need to be present. EXAMPLE(S): 2 Skin patches NOTE(S): Default is 1. Normally used during study design to indicate number of parts that will be used in a study. For example 100 study subjects with 3-5 skin patches.
